Synthesized Data

    DT::datatable(
        options = list(dom = "rtip")
        , rownames = FALSE
        , extensions = c("Responsive", "Scroller")
        ) |>
    DT::formatStyle(columns =1:4, textAlign = "center")

Continuity Results

Using a timeout of 10 (days) and imputed groups defined by columns join_key and src, the data was consolidated into a series of larger epochs marked by start and end dates. The data will be processed under.

data.table::copy(test_data.01) |>
    continuity(
        map_fields = c(join_key, src)
        , time_fields = c(date.start, date.end)
        , boundary_name = episode
        , timeout = 10
        , archipelago = TRUE
        , show.all = !TRUE
        ) |>
    DT::datatable(
        options = list(dom = "rtip")
        , rownames = FALSE
        , extensions = c("Responsive", "Scroller")
        ) |>
    DT::formatStyle(columns = 1:5, textAlign = "center")

A Final Note

There is an additional consideration that is not addressed by the continuity function: Is the timeout choice of 10 the best choice given the data? Answering that requires comparing imputed “islands” to some independent, adjudicating set of data or domain expert that can provide an assessment of reasonableness. An alternative method would be to set the timeout by means of statistical analysis. See Break Signal for an example.
